title: Running: Gulf to Gulf Relay set for Saturday
text:
Previous Next 
NAPLES, Fla. - The Gulf to Gulf Relay presented by Gulf Coast Runners will be Saturday at 6 a.m. at Cambier Park in Naples. 
The Gulf to Gulf Relay race starts and ending at Cambier Park and will wind through Naples up to Bonita Springs, Fort Myers Beach, and then turn around at the Sanibel Causeway. 
Up to 30 six-person teams will be allowed to register for this event. Each team member will receive a long sleeve quarter-zip custom logo shirt. Pizza and awards will be at Cambier Park at the conclusion of the race. For more information, go to gcrunner.org. Copyright 2015 Journal Media Group. All rights reserved.
